{"title_page": "Ardnamurchan Point", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox landform\n| water             = \n| name              = Ardnamurchan Point\n| other_name        = \n| photo             = Ardnamurchan point.jpg\n| photo_width       = \n| photo_alt         = \n| photo_caption     = Ardnamurchan Point across Eilean Chaluim Cille\n| map               = UK Scotland\n| map_width         = \n| map_caption       = \n| map_alt           = \n| relief            = 1\n| label             = \n| label_position    = \n| mark              = \n| marker_size       = \n| location          = [[Highland (council area)|Highland]], [[Scotland]]\n| grid_ref          = \n| grid_ref_UK       = NM416674\n| grid_ref_Ireland  = \n| coordinates       = {{Coord|56.726|-6.224|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_ref   = \n| range             = \n| part_of           = \n| water_bodies      = \n| elevation_ft      = <!-- or |elevation_m = -->\n| elevation_ref     = \n| surface_elevation_ft = <!-- or |surface_elevation_m = -->\n| surface_elevation_ref =\n| highest_point     = \n| highest_elevation = \n| highest_coords    = \n| length            = \n| width             = \n| area              = <!-- {{Convert|NN|ha|acres}} -->\n| depth             = \n| drop              = \n| formed_by         = \n| geology           = <!-- or |type = -->\n| age               = \n| orogeny           = \n| volcanic_arc/belt = \n| volcanic_arc      = \n| volcanic_belt     = \n| volcanic_field    = \n| eruption          = \n| last_eruption     = \n| topo              = \n| operator          = \n| designation       = \n| website           = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n}}\n'''Ardnamurchan Point''' ({{lang-gd|Ard na Murchan}}, meaning \"the hill of the great sea\") is an isolated [[peninsula]] in [[Highland (council area)|Highland]], [[Scotland]] where the [[Ardnamurchan Lighthouse]] is situated.\n\n==Location==\nArdnamurchan Point lies at the western end of the [[Ardnamurchan]] [[peninsula]] in [[Lochaber]], [[Highland (council area)|Highland]], [[Scotland]]. [[Ardnamurchan Lighthouse]] is here, {{convert|1.1|km}} north of [[Corrachadh M\u00f2r]], the [[Extreme points of the United Kingdom|most westerly point]] on the island of [[Great Britain]], which is a few metres further west than the Point.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.undiscoveredscotland.co.uk/kilchoan/ardnamurchanpoint/index.html | title=Ardnamurchan Point| publisher=Undiscovered Scotland| accessdate=18 September 2009}}</ref> The nearest settlement is the small village, [[Achosnich]].\n\nThe point lies seven miles south of the island of [[Muck, Scotland|Muck]], with [[Eigg]] and [[R\u00f9m]] a few miles further to the north. [[Coll]] is situated nine miles to the west, and [[Isle of Mull|Mull]] is five miles south.\n\n==Cultural references==\nThe contemporary Scottish composer [[Judith Weir]] has written an 8-minute piece for two pianos called ''Ardnamurchan Point''.<ref>Broadcast on [[BBC Radio 3]]'s [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01r0ynt ''Saturday Classics'' program] (2 March 2013)</ref>\nThe location is featured in [[Shipping Forecast]] broadcast by [[BBC Radio 4]] (on behalf of the [[Maritime and Coastguard Agency]]), where it is one of the [[Inshore coastal areas of the United Kingdom]].\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.ardnamurchanlighthouse.com/ Ardnamurchan Lighthouse] - official site\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Headlands of Scotland]]\n[[Category:Ardnamurchan]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox landform\n| water             = \n| name              = Ardnamurchan Point\n| other_name        = \n| photo             = Ardnamurchan point.jpg\n| photo_width       = \n| photo_alt         = \n| photo_caption     = Ardnamurchan Point across Eilean Chaluim Cille\n| map               = UK Scotland\n| map_width         = \n| map_caption       = \n| map_alt           = \n| relief            = 1\n| label             = \n| label_position    = \n| mark              = \n| marker_size       = \n| location          = [[Highland (council area)|Highland]], [[Scotland]]\n| grid_ref          = \n| grid_ref_UK       = NM416674\n| grid_ref_Ireland  = \n| coordinates       = {{Coord|56.726|-6.224|display=inline,title}}\n| coordinates_ref   = \n| range             = \n| part_of           = \n| water_bodies      = \n| elevation_ft      = <!-- or |elevation_m = -->\n| elevation_ref     = \n| surface_elevation_ft = <!-- or |surface_elevation_m = -->\n| surface_elevation_ref =\n| highest_point     = \n| highest_elevation = \n| highest_coords    = \n| length            = \n| width             = \n| area              = <!-- {{Convert|NN|ha|acres}} -->\n| depth             = \n| drop              = \n| formed_by         = \n| geology           = <!-- or |type = -->\n| age               = \n| orogeny           = \n| volcanic_arc/belt = \n| volcanic_arc      = \n| volcanic_belt     = \n| volcanic_field    = \n| eruption          = \n| last_eruption     = \n| topo              = \n| operator          = \n| designation       = \n| website           = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n}}\n'''Ardnamurchan Point''' ({{lang-gd|Ard na Murchan}}, meaning \"the hill of the great sea\") is an isolated [[peninsula]] in [[Highland (council area)|Highland]], [[Scotland]] where the [[Ardnamurchan Lighthouse]] is situated.\n\n==Location==\nArdnamurchan Point lies at the western end of the [[Ardnamurchan]] [[peninsula]] in [[Lochaber]], [[Highland (council area)|Highland]], [[Scotland]]. [[Ardnamurchan Lighthouse]] is here, {{convert|1.1|km}} north of [[Corrachadh M\u00f2r]], the [[Extreme points of the United Kingdom|most westerly point]] on the island of [[Great Britain]], which is a few metres further west than the Point.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.undiscoveredscotland.co.uk/kilchoan/ardnamurchanpoint/index.html | title=Ardnamurchan Point| publisher=Undiscovered Scotland| accessdate=18 September 2009}}</ref> The nearest settlement is the small village, [[Achosnich]].\n\nThe point lies seven miles south of the island of [[Muck, Scotland|Muck]], with [[Eigg]] and [[R\u00f9m]] a few miles further to the north. [[Coll]] is situated nine miles to the west, and [[Isle of Mull|Mull]] is five miles south.\n\n==Cultural references==\nThe contemporary Scottish composer [[Judith Weir]] has written an 8-minute piece for two pianos called ''Ardnamurchan Point''.<ref>Broadcast on [[BBC Radio 3]]'s [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b01r0ynt ''Saturday Classics'' program] (2 March 2013)</ref>\nThe location is featured in [[Shipping Forecast]] broadcast by [[BBC Radio 4]] (on behalf of the [[Maritime and Coastguard Agency]]), where it is used in the forecast as the name of one of the [[Inshore coastal areas of the United Kingdom]].\n\n==Notes==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.ardnamurchanlighthouse.com/ Ardnamurchan Lighthouse] - official site\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Headlands of Scotland]]\n[[Category:Ardnamurchan]]\n", "name_user": "Joelster7455", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eCultural references:Took some unnecessary words away from the last sentence", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ardnamurchan_Point"}
